{
  "texts": [
    "Mixed strategies combine both time-based and datadriven approaches.",
    "In a mixed-based strategy, researchers decide to stop reviewing after a certain number of abstracts have been reviewed and a certain threshold of consecutive irrelevant records have been found (Hamel et al., 2021; Yu & Menzies, 2019).",
    "The use of these heuristic approaches in ML-assisted systematic reviews in education and educational psychology research is not uncommon.",
    "For example, Guan et al. (2023) used a data-driven strategy to stop the reviewing process in a systematic review of educational data ethics.",
    "Similarly, Zhang et al. (2023) used a time-based strategy to stop screening in a systematic review of school-based mental health interventions."
  ]
}